                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Ejryuu wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
I almost always pull for any group I'm in, regardless of content.  Just tash, run back to group, and cast mem blur </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I personally find, post BoT/HoH, pre-OOW, which is where i play most of the time, that a pet works wonders to intercept the mob u pulled.  The tank will taunt and often pick up your tash agro + 1 right off the bat, giving them a solid agro lead on the rest of the group, and the rule of 4 wont kick in till 2 ppl aside from you, your pet, and the tank get on the hatelist, which will generally take longer than it takes the tank to generate more agro than the pull-tash.  The only exception to this is with summoning mobs, and that's only some of the time, this happens when 2 other ppl who are on the ball get on the hatelist before the tank can generate tash + agro either thru a taunt or thru other means.  Even in these cases, i generally only get summoned one out of 2 or 3 mobs, and they go after the tank before they can get their 2nd round of swings off... if they even get 1 round...
<br />

<br />
This method's got the advantage of giving the tank tash + 1 agro much of the time early in the fight, allowing everyone else to be more agressive, and eliminating the chance of the tank hitting some agro method, and ur blur landing a split second later, which while not likely if you get your timing down, can happen if you're experiencing lag, or if your rythem's off.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
