                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rhythm?  What's that?  I'm assuming by pet you mean a charmed pet.  I trust Shiny  shiny bob to tank about as much as I trust a ranger with a bow to not break mez : /  Yar, pull with tash, sick pet on immediately and start the slow.  Ideally, you should have pet, tank, snarer, and yourself on the aggro list during the slowing process.  By the time anyone else jumps on, you should already be anticipating mem blur if your tank hasn't managed to snag enough aggro.  You run into problems when overzealous "lesser" classes (read: rogues, magicians, wizards, bards....pretty much everything! &gt;&lt; ) jump in prematurely.  Also let the pet take the lead by taking the first few hits instead of the tank so that the healer doesn't have to panic right away.  Besides, clerics looooove an 18.5k crit CH that actually heals for that much = )</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
