<br />

<br />
The problem here is more of a lookup one.
<br />

<br />
"Find all/any mobs that have X on their hate list" isn't something any EQ code needed before this point.  Hate lists change the behaviour of the creature, and the player's data structure doesn't need to know about it. (unless I missed something)
<br />

<br />
Other than that problem, making SW go off on every mob with the player on their hate list wouldn't be much of a problem.  It can't remove people form the hate list of a mob...
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">edit</span> Fade and FD effects require a lookup from PC to "All creatures with PC on it's hate list".  So coding a SW as a "target PC loses X hate on all mob's hate lists" is doable.
<br />

<br />
Players are rarely on more than 1 mob's hate list anyhow.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
